Covid-19 Report

Ömür Özkir

April 10, 2020

The dataset

The dataset used is available at Github under https://ramikrispin.github.io/coronavirus/ and updated daily (but might be delayed by up to a day).

The source additionally provides the data as csv file and also offers a comprehensive dashboard based on this dataset.

The Last 24 Hours

Worldwide Confirmed Cases

Total cases by country

Confirmed New Cases

These numbers are only as good as the amount of testing done and should be taken with a grain of salt.

Also keep in mind that there is a significant delay between being infected and having the results of the test. Testing in most countries will only be done once symptoms appear and the test itself can also take a few days. The numbers basically reflect the state of a few days in the past (the exact number of days varies from country to country).

April 8 The number of new cases is still rising in the US, to 32829 new cases. France saw a drop in new cases while Germany saw a slight increase in new cases.

April 7

The US is still leading the charts with a terrifying number of almost 30.000 new cases.

France has the second-highest number of new cases, with more than 11.000 new cases.

New Deaths due to COVID-19

April 8 The UK is experiencing a wave of new deaths (940 deaths today), while the US continues to have the most deaths caused by COVID-19 (1973 today).

April 7

France is experiencing a sad rise in deaths caused by the corona virus, 1417 today, only overshadowed by the deaths in the US, which lost 1939 people to the virus today.

New Recovered Cases

April 8 The number of todays’ recovered cases in Germany rose to over 10000 and Spain also seems to slowly recover.

April 7

Germany could report 7381 recovered cases, the most world-wide.
